WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:03.213
Welcome to the James River Church podcast.

00:03.634 --> 00:10.984
You're about to hear another inspirational message from Pastor David Lindel, executive ministry pastor at James River Church.

00:11.004 --> 00:14.970
It's our prayer that this message is an encouragement and blessing to your life.

00:16.112 --> 00:23.762
Well, tonight I want to jump into the Word of God very quickly because then we're going to spend a little time in the altar.

00:24.323 --> 00:29.330
But I want to talk to you from the subject, discouraged, not defeated.

00:31.362 --> 00:34.185
discouraged, not defeated.

00:36.047 --> 00:43.234
And the reason that I've titled this in that way is because a lot of times discouragement feels like defeat.

00:43.555 --> 00:51.343
And because it feels like defeat, we begin to inhabit the identity of a defeated person.

00:53.925 --> 00:58.610
It's okay to be discouraged, but you are not defeated.

01:01.570 --> 01:04.054
It's okay to feel the weight of a situation.

01:04.114 --> 01:17.653
It's okay to walk through a valley, but just be reminded that even though you walk through the valley of the shadow of death, you will fear no evil because you're not defeated.

01:17.953 --> 01:18.914
Why are you not defeated?

01:18.975 --> 01:19.976
Because he's not defeated.

01:22.800 --> 01:24.843
Discouraged, not defeated.

01:26.445 --> 01:29.970
I'm going to take you to Psalm chapter

01:30.210 --> 01:43.869
42 here in just a moment because I know that there are people in the room and watching online and you came in tonight heavy because the season has been heavy.

01:46.432 --> 01:48.074
It's not just a day.

01:48.114 --> 01:53.722
It's not the kind of heaviness that is fixed by a good night's sleep.

01:55.965 --> 01:56.766
It's hung on.

01:58.809 --> 01:59.730
It's been difficult.

02:00.898 --> 02:07.107
There are layers to what you're feeling and layers to what you're walking through.

02:09.030 --> 02:23.673
Yet, we can never, ever, ever look at our situation and then look at the Word of God and say, yeah, but, yeah, well, okay, well, thanks, David.

02:24.394 --> 02:25.035
It's not David.

02:25.275 --> 02:26.978
If it was David, you could say, yeah, thanks, David.

02:28.360 --> 02:29.842
But if it's the Holy Spirit,

02:30.914 --> 02:49.353
speaking to you through the inspired Word of God, his authoritative revelation of himself, then that ought to refrain and that ought to reposition the way that we're walking through our situation.

02:51.217 --> 02:51.858
Because

02:52.290 --> 03:05.027
It's authoritative means we have the responsibility if we are children of God of coming under its authority, and that includes the way we're processing our situation.

03:06.348 --> 03:09.492
We don't get a claim and identity that the word of God doesn't give us.

03:09.753 --> 03:10.313
You don't get one.

03:10.353 --> 03:12.937
You don't get that vote.

03:12.957 --> 03:16.662
You don't get a claim defeat when the word of God says that's not where you live.

03:17.623 --> 03:19.986
You don't let it get discouragement.

03:20.354 --> 03:28.327
morph into something that it should never be, which means you have to confront the way you're feeling with the Word of God.

03:30.010 --> 03:35.739
This is so powerful when you go to Psalm 42, because the psalm this doesn't pretend everything is okay.

03:37.222 --> 03:41.188
Look at this, Psalm 42, we're going to read the whole passage real quick.

03:41.208 --> 03:45.195
As the deer longs for streams of water, so I long for you, O God.

03:46.537 --> 03:47.218
I thirst

03:47.490 --> 03:51.894
For God, the living God, when can I go and stand before Him?

03:52.535 --> 04:02.064
Day and night, I have only tears for food while my enemies continually taught me, saying, where is this God of yours?

04:03.445 --> 04:06.588
My heart is breaking, as I remember how it used to be.

04:06.688 --> 04:17.298
I walked among the crowds of worshipers, leaving a great procession to the house of God, singing for joy, and giving thanks amid the sound of a great celebration

04:17.442 --> 04:20.887
Why am I discouraged?

04:23.050 --> 04:24.633
Why is my heart so sad?

04:26.516 --> 04:28.018
I'll put my hope in God.

04:28.038 --> 04:30.562
I will praise Him again, my Savior and my God.

04:31.763 --> 04:44.242
Now, I am deeply discouraged, but I will remember you even from distant Mount Herman, the source of the Jordan from

04:44.418 --> 04:52.130
Mount Meeras, I hear the tumult of the raging seas as your waves and surging tides sweep over me.

04:52.310 --> 04:57.318
But each day the Lord pours his unfailing love upon me.

04:57.338 --> 05:09.015
And through each night I sing his songs, praying to God who gives me life, oh God my rock, I cry, why have you forgotten me?

05:09.095 --> 05:10.898
Why must I wander

05:11.266 --> 05:13.870
around in grief, oppressed by my enemies.

05:13.990 --> 05:15.893
Their taunts break my bones.

05:16.573 --> 05:18.717
They scoff, where is this God of yours?

05:20.078 --> 05:21.200
Why am I discouraged?

05:22.902 --> 05:25.186
Why is my heart so sad?

05:25.967 --> 05:27.429
I will put my hope in God.

05:28.610 --> 05:35.060
I will praise Him again, my Savior and my God."

05:36.702 --> 05:39.666
This is a powerful, powerful Psalm.

05:40.514 --> 05:44.138
because of what it holds intention.

05:46.401 --> 05:49.684
It is not just David saying, why am I discouraged?

05:49.704 --> 05:51.386
Here's all the reasons I shouldn't be discouraged.

05:52.508 --> 05:56.993
It is David simultaneously saying, here's all the reasons I'm discouraged.

05:57.693 --> 05:58.735
Why am I discouraged?

06:00.637 --> 06:02.038
That's an interesting combination.

06:04.401 --> 06:08.786
And yet, the psalmness is incredibly instructive.

06:09.762 --> 06:13.327
in this Psalm because we're going to read it backwards.

06:14.889 --> 06:24.101
I don't know if you know this, but the way Hebrew is structured, it doesn't read top to bottom.

06:24.141 --> 06:28.847
A lot of it is circular, especially in the Psalms, obviously, poetic language.

06:30.409 --> 06:36.818
The Psalm this is making a holistic point, and at some points, if you're reading a Psalm top to bottom,

06:38.018 --> 06:41.601
It's not actually in order of like a thought process.

06:41.662 --> 06:50.390
It's not an argument being built necessarily in the way that we might think about that, like A, B, C, D, E, F, G. It's the whole thing.

06:52.312 --> 07:01.801
So there's some value in taking this Psalm piece by piece because David gives us six principles for dealing with discouragement.

07:03.022 --> 07:06.866
Six principles that if you will do them, if you will,

07:07.106 --> 07:07.967
Embrace them.

07:09.048 --> 07:09.849
I promise you.

07:11.270 --> 07:15.434
I promise you it'll make a massive difference.

07:15.454 --> 07:16.555
Okay, first principle.

07:18.257 --> 07:21.300
Bring your questions to God.

07:21.320 --> 07:23.222
Oh God, my rock, I cry.

07:23.262 --> 07:24.763
Why have you forgotten me?

07:24.803 --> 07:26.145
That's a big question right there.

07:27.626 --> 07:33.432
Now, if we took a poll in the room and we would say, has God forgotten David?

07:34.273 --> 07:35.794
Yes or no?

07:37.282 --> 07:41.146
I think we would get almost 100% of people to say, no, he hasn't forgotten him.

07:41.987 --> 07:46.212
I actually think David, if he were in the room, would raise his hand.

07:47.834 --> 07:48.795
Which tells you what?

07:50.757 --> 07:55.102
He knows it up here, but he doesn't feel it in here.

07:57.705 --> 07:59.047
Have you ever known something?

08:00.769 --> 08:05.554
You know the truth, but you just don't feel it.

08:08.418 --> 08:09.859
God, why have you forgotten me?

08:09.960 --> 08:13.583
Why must I wander around in grief, oppressed by my enemies?"

08:16.126 --> 08:18.628
He's going to tell us he's got people persecuting him.

08:18.648 --> 08:21.151
He's got people saying things about him.

08:21.171 --> 08:22.732
He's got people throwing rocks at him.

08:22.752 --> 08:24.274
He's got all of that going on.

08:25.195 --> 08:28.038
His question is, God, why are you letting that happen?

08:30.360 --> 08:32.943
God, why are you letting this go on in my life?

08:33.763 --> 08:36.306
It feels like you've forgotten.

08:36.578 --> 08:39.762
I know you haven't, but it feels like you've forgotten.

08:39.782 --> 08:41.304
Why does it feel that way, Lord?

08:41.324 --> 08:43.307
Why does it feel that way to me right now?

08:44.168 --> 08:47.192
Some of you, you know that question.

08:49.475 --> 08:50.997
I want to tell you something right now.

08:51.697 --> 08:53.340
God can handle your questions.

08:55.542 --> 08:57.925
God's not intimidated by your questions.

08:59.227 --> 09:04.594
God's not freaked out by your fear.

09:04.706 --> 09:08.670
Messed over when you come down and go, I don't understand why this is going on.

09:09.110 --> 09:14.775
The problem is a lot of times we are not willing to be honest in the presence of the Lord.

09:16.777 --> 09:24.264
And David is demonstrating a holy honesty to say, God, I don't understand.

09:24.304 --> 09:25.946
And here's the good news.

09:26.006 --> 09:34.674
What he does is instead of taking his questions to his neighbor and instead of taking his questions to his, you know, to the captain of the guard or whoever,

09:35.746 --> 09:36.407
What is he doing?

09:36.808 --> 09:40.154
He's taking his questions to the best possible source.

09:41.196 --> 09:42.398
He's taking them to God.

09:43.380 --> 09:46.646
And when he takes them to God, he's not pretending nothing is wrong.

09:46.686 --> 09:49.070
He's not pretending he doesn't feel this way.

09:49.090 --> 09:49.972
He's not pretending.

09:50.252 --> 09:52.016
He doesn't wonder why it's happening.

09:52.296 --> 09:53.298
He's honest.

09:55.778 --> 10:02.725
Some of you are discouraged, some of you are wondering what's going on, but you haven't poured out your heart to God in prayer.

10:03.085 --> 10:07.269
Can I tell you, David is giving you a picture of how to do that well.

10:09.591 --> 10:25.426
One of the best things you could do is to say, God, I haven't said how I'm feeling to you, and I'm pretty sure it's not right, and I know it's not true, and yet I have to tell you what's going on in my heart right now, because I need your help.

10:27.266 --> 10:28.788
He's not just venting to the Lord.

10:29.990 --> 10:31.332
David knows he's off.

10:32.534 --> 10:35.278
He knows he shouldn't feel this way.

10:35.318 --> 10:40.045
What he's feeling doesn't line up with the Word of God, but he's saying, God, I have to express it to you.

10:40.326 --> 10:41.928
I have to tell you what's going on.

10:42.229 --> 10:44.151
I'm going to just let you in on something.

10:44.171 --> 10:45.113
You have to do the same thing.

10:46.194 --> 10:47.096
You have to do the same thing.

10:48.017 --> 10:56.530
If you're going to deal with your discouragement and it's going to actually be dealt with, there's got to come a point where you level with the Lord.

10:56.866 --> 10:59.630
And you say, God, I'm struggling here.

11:00.131 --> 11:01.453
God, I'm tired.

11:01.853 --> 11:03.075
God, I'm worn out.

11:03.215 --> 11:07.181
God, I don't know how I'm going to make it through this next season.

11:07.482 --> 11:08.163
And here's the thing.

11:08.223 --> 11:13.571
When you do that, there's something that happens in your heart, and it's really good.

11:14.472 --> 11:14.973
It's really good.

11:16.014 --> 11:22.164
So he first starts by bringing his questions to God, but then he anchors himself in God's love.

11:23.526 --> 11:26.450
But each day, the Lord pours his unfailing love

11:27.522 --> 11:27.922
on me.

11:29.744 --> 11:34.169
Unfailing love means this, that God's love isn't fickle or fragile.

11:35.070 --> 11:35.891
Are you thankful for that?

11:37.333 --> 11:43.900
I'm thankful that God doesn't wake up one day and go, oh, yeah, I'm kind of tired of this whole thing.

11:44.500 --> 11:45.361
You mess up a lot.

11:47.624 --> 11:49.866
Because none of us would survive that litmus test.

11:50.387 --> 11:52.709
None of us.

11:52.729 --> 11:53.850
God's love isn't fickle.

11:54.090 --> 11:54.851
It's unfailing.

11:55.952 --> 11:57.394
God's love isn't fragile.

11:58.082 --> 11:59.063
You can't break it.

12:00.425 --> 12:03.029
He doesn't love you more today than he loved you yesterday.

12:03.089 --> 12:07.315
He loves you the same tomorrow, the next day, and the next day.

12:07.555 --> 12:11.621
He couldn't love you anymore and he couldn't love you any less because his love is unfailing.

12:12.002 --> 12:13.704
It's boundless for his children.

12:13.724 --> 12:26.322
And yet there has to be a reminder in your heart that you have to constantly go to the Word of God to say, God, I know this is true because here's the thing, it's great to bring your questions to God.

12:26.530 --> 12:39.230
But if you don't then follow up your questions by reminding yourself of the truth, then you lock yourself out from the answers that God would want to give you.

12:40.912 --> 12:45.880
Because the answers to your questions are always going to be rooted in the truth of his word.

12:47.603 --> 12:49.446
They're always going to be rooted in the truth of his word.

12:49.906 --> 12:51.449
And his word is rooted where?

12:52.550 --> 12:54.834
His word is rooted in his character.

12:56.194 --> 13:03.863
So you have to not just go to his word, but then you have to then back up the truck to the character and the nature of Almighty God.

13:04.324 --> 13:06.226
Because that's what his word is testifying to.

13:06.446 --> 13:09.910
And you have to say, God, I not only know your word says it, I know who you are.

13:11.192 --> 13:13.655
I've experienced your unfailing love.

13:13.675 --> 13:21.244
I've experienced your never giving up, never stopping, always ready to give me a big hug, always ready to come to my rescue love.

13:22.325 --> 13:23.186
I've experienced it.

13:24.354 --> 13:29.359
You've got to anchor your life in His love.

13:29.399 --> 13:33.403
Here's the thing, discouragement whispers your abandoned.

13:36.325 --> 13:40.910
God's love shouts, no, you're not.

13:41.570 --> 13:45.554
He promised, I will never leave you or forsake you.

13:45.854 --> 13:47.576
My faithfulness is great.

13:48.457 --> 13:53.842
That's the God who cares about you, but you have to ground yourself.

13:54.274 --> 13:58.899
You have to anchor yourself in his love, which means you have to anchor yourself in his character.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.720
Number three, sing.

14:00.760 --> 14:03.683
This is so good, especially at night.

14:05.565 --> 14:06.546
Sing, especially at night.

14:06.586 --> 14:07.787
Some of y'all, we just did that.

14:07.927 --> 14:09.049
It's nighttime and we're singing.

14:09.129 --> 14:09.349
Okay.

14:10.110 --> 14:13.813
But each day, the Lord pours his unfailing love upon me.

14:14.514 --> 14:17.277
And through each night, I sing his songs.

14:19.699 --> 14:20.280
I love that.

14:21.180 --> 14:22.802
So when we were proofreading my notes,

14:23.042 --> 14:26.425
One of the guys who helps me goes, sing especially at night.

14:27.486 --> 14:28.647
It's like, yeah, you don't do that.

14:29.969 --> 14:30.829
That's so normal.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.892
It's like, it's a really normal thing to do.

14:34.413 --> 14:39.758
Christians do a lot of really abnormal things, by the way, which is good.

14:39.778 --> 14:42.440
I don't want to be like everybody else.

14:44.763 --> 14:47.745
If you do what everybody else does, you'll get what everybody else gets.

14:50.388 --> 14:51.689
I don't want whatever you want, y'all skits.

14:51.749 --> 14:52.690
I don't want that.

14:53.506 --> 14:55.108
I want what God's word says I get.

14:55.128 --> 14:57.350
I mean, call me crazy.

14:57.370 --> 15:01.795
I serve the God of the universe.

15:01.815 --> 15:04.237
Like I would like to operate on his terms, not in the world's terms.

15:04.277 --> 15:06.159
I would like to operate on his terms and on my terms.

15:07.220 --> 15:08.982
His terms are way better than my terms.

15:11.204 --> 15:13.046
So sing.

15:14.488 --> 15:15.429
Do what other people don't do.

15:16.330 --> 15:18.051
So why does the Psalm this say?

15:18.071 --> 15:20.594
Because this is incredibly intentional language.

15:21.410 --> 15:23.673
Seeing especially at night.

15:24.254 --> 15:26.678
Night is when discouragement gets loud.

15:27.799 --> 15:28.621
Have you ever noticed that?

15:29.362 --> 15:30.724
Everything is worse at night.

15:31.825 --> 15:33.368
Everything is worse at night.

15:34.129 --> 15:35.150
You're tired at night.

15:35.371 --> 15:36.472
You're worn out at night.

15:36.753 --> 15:39.236
The kids are louder and have to be put to bed at night.

15:40.038 --> 15:40.618
Every night.

15:41.199 --> 15:41.680
Every night.

15:41.860 --> 15:43.182
I have to put my kids to bed.

15:43.603 --> 15:45.786
And every night, they're surprised.

15:48.911 --> 15:49.271
Dead.

15:50.032 --> 15:51.154
I don't want to go to bed.

15:52.738 --> 15:53.639
We did this last night.

15:55.622 --> 15:56.504
We did it the night before.

15:56.564 --> 16:00.650
And newsflash, we gonna do it tomorrow night, too.

16:03.494 --> 16:04.355
Everything's worse at night.

16:06.038 --> 16:07.920
Your fears get bigger at night.

16:08.441 --> 16:11.065
Your anxiety gets greater at night.

16:12.387 --> 16:15.251
All of a sudden you start replaying conversations from the day.

16:16.213 --> 16:20.479
I'm always smarter on the replay than I am in real time.

16:21.220 --> 16:22.482
Like I'm like, well,

16:23.010 --> 16:28.480
Oh my goodness.

16:28.681 --> 16:29.823
This has really happened.

16:30.384 --> 16:31.165
This is so sad.

16:32.047 --> 16:36.054
But Becky has come back in our master bedroom closet and she was like, are you on the phone?

16:39.942 --> 16:40.122
No.

16:42.286 --> 16:43.288
Who are you talking to?

16:43.308 --> 16:46.674
I am verbally processing.

16:48.194 --> 16:54.160
AKA, I am replaying a conversation and I'm thinking of all the really smart things I should have said.

16:55.882 --> 16:58.584
Oh, you think that?

16:58.644 --> 16:58.744
No.

16:58.764 --> 16:59.865
I know you guys do this.

16:59.946 --> 17:00.366
I know this.

17:00.466 --> 17:02.248
I'm not the only crazy person here.

17:04.550 --> 17:08.714
So this is why you have to do something different than everybody else does at night.

17:09.835 --> 17:10.516
And here's the thing.

17:10.556 --> 17:16.722
We are our own worst enemies because we come home at night and not only do we replay,

17:17.378 --> 17:21.262
the defeats of the day are greatest hits.

17:21.282 --> 17:23.965
Not only do we do that, but then what do we do?

17:25.447 --> 17:27.109
We doom scroll social media.

17:28.090 --> 17:29.431
We binge watching Netflix.

17:30.252 --> 17:32.134
We just turn on the TV and zone out.

17:34.737 --> 17:36.399
I ain't to tell you, that ain't helping you.

17:37.600 --> 17:40.123
We are increasing our own anxiety.

17:40.463 --> 17:42.485
We're making it worse.

17:43.687 --> 17:45.649
You watch the news, you'll be more discouraged.

17:46.089 --> 17:46.930
I'm just telling you.

17:47.106 --> 17:49.029
It's not like an encouragement factory.

17:49.650 --> 17:51.493
That's not why they make the news.

17:51.693 --> 17:53.716
It's like, here's the best things that happen today.

17:54.057 --> 17:56.821
I don't know if it's the opposite.

17:58.283 --> 18:03.151
When you're discouraged, what you have to do is you have to do something different than what the world does.

18:04.313 --> 18:10.162
That's why when you get home, you ought to fill your heart and your house with worship.

18:10.818 --> 18:19.850
You ought to turn on something that lifts your eyes above your situation and get your eyes off all the things that should discourage you, could it discourage you?

18:20.231 --> 18:22.254
And say, God, I'm getting my eyes on you.

18:22.314 --> 18:27.981
I'm lifting my eyes out of the storm, seeing especially at night.

18:29.183 --> 18:30.685
So this is great.

18:31.386 --> 18:33.929
Worship does what discouragement hates.

18:35.351 --> 18:36.413
It puts truth in your mouth.

18:37.795 --> 18:38.756
Put truth in your mouth.

18:39.317 --> 18:40.018
Put truth in your mouth.

18:40.038 --> 18:40.338
Okay.

18:40.770 --> 18:44.273
Number four, preach to yourself, Psalm 4225.

18:45.615 --> 18:47.436
Why am I discouraged?

18:47.517 --> 18:48.978
Why is my heart so sad?

18:49.238 --> 18:50.459
I will put my hope in God.

18:50.499 --> 18:52.341
I will praise him again, my Savior.

18:52.882 --> 18:53.763
What's David doing?

18:53.783 --> 18:56.385
He's doing what I do in my master bedroom closet.

18:56.665 --> 18:58.067
Oh, I feel so good.

18:58.787 --> 19:00.589
Me and the psalmist, we on the same wavelength.

19:01.290 --> 19:02.831
Preach to yourself.

19:04.073 --> 19:05.754
Talk to yourself.

19:06.475 --> 19:09.778
Some of you, your situation,

19:10.114 --> 19:15.660
and your exhaustion from your situation is actually not exhaustion from what happened.

19:16.801 --> 19:21.126
It's exhaustion from what you are telling yourself about what happened.

19:24.670 --> 19:35.922
It is, you make it worse, you're reliving it, you're reliving it, you're relaying it, you're letting it write the narrative again and again and again, because discouragement will talk to you.

19:37.730 --> 19:39.572
There is a narrative to discouragement.

19:39.632 --> 19:41.534
There's a storyline to discouragement.

19:43.075 --> 19:45.437
And if you let it, it'll run you.

19:47.019 --> 19:58.370
David Martin Lloyd-Jones in his book, Spiritual Depression, writes this, you have you realized that most of your unhappiness in life is due to the fact that you are listening to yourself instead of talking to yourself.

19:59.791 --> 20:03.735
Take those thoughts that come to you the moment you wake up in the morning.

20:04.556 --> 20:06.578
You have not originated them.

20:06.722 --> 20:07.824
But they are talking to you.

20:08.906 --> 20:10.850
They bring back the problems of yesterday.

20:10.910 --> 20:12.673
Somebody is talking.

20:12.834 --> 20:13.775
Who's talking to you?

20:14.056 --> 20:15.459
Your self is talking to you.

20:15.499 --> 20:21.470
Now, this man's treatment in Psalm 42, which we're looking at, was this.

20:21.650 --> 20:27.762
Instead of allowing this self to talk to him, he started talking to himself.

